> assistant
Yes — the issue is in the selector you use when registering the folding provider.

You register it with:

```ts
vscode.languages.registerFoldingRangeProvider('convo-lang', {
```

But your language id in `package.json` is:

```json
"id": "source.convo"
```

And elsewhere you also use that same id, for example:

```ts
languages.registerDocumentLinkProvider(
    'source.convo',
    new ConvoDocumentLinkProvider()
)
```

So VS Code never associates the folding provider with Convo documents, which is why `provideFoldingRanges` is never called.

## Fix

Change this:

```ts
const r=vscode.languages.registerFoldingRangeProvider('convo-lang', {
```

to this:

```ts
const r=vscode.languages.registerFoldingRangeProvider('source.convo', {
```

## Updated file

<FILE_CONTENT name="folding-provider.ts" target-output-path="../../packages/convo-lang-tools/lsp/client/src/folding-provider.ts" fenced>
```ts
import * as vscode from 'vscode';

export const createFoldingProvider=()=>{
    return vscode.languages.registerFoldingRangeProvider('source.convo', {
        provideFoldingRanges(document, context, token) {
            return findTagRanges(document);
        }
    });
}

function findTagRanges(document:vscode.TextDocument):vscode.FoldingRange[] {
    const ranges:vscode.FoldingRange[]=[];
    const stack:{name:string,line:number}[]=[];

    const tagRegex=/<(\/)?([\w-]+)[^>/]*(\/?\s*)>/g;

    for(let i=0;i<document.lineCount;i++){
        const lineText=document.lineAt(i).text;
        let match:RegExpExecArray|null;

        while((match=tagRegex.exec(lineText))!==null){
            const [,isClosing,tagName,isSelfClosing]=match;
            if(!tagName){
                continue;
            }

            if(isSelfClosing){
                continue;
            }

            if(isClosing){
                const index=stack.map(s=>s.name).lastIndexOf(tagName);
                if(index!==-1){
                    const openTag=stack.splice(index,1)[0];
                    if(openTag && openTag.line!==i){
                        ranges.push(new vscode.FoldingRange(openTag.line,i));
                    }
                }
            }else{
                stack.push({name:tagName,line:i});
            }
        }
    }

    return ranges;
}
```
</FILE_CONTENT>

## One more note

You may also want to use a full document selector object instead of a string, e.g.:

```ts
vscode.languages.registerFoldingRangeProvider(
    {language:'source.convo',scheme:'file'},
    ...
)
```

But the main bug is definitely the wrong language id.


